parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The oil warning light illuminates
the vehicle consumes a quart of oil every 2
000 miles
the oil level drops significantly between oil changes
and the vehicle may emit black smoke from the exhaust pipe.

fails to accelerate
or stalls in an intersection
and the dealer may indicate that the transmission needs to be replaced at a high mileage (e.g.
000 miles).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to surge forward, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward with high engine revs
especially when slowly pulling into a driveway or driving up to a mailbox.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash.

as these complaints are related to the recall and lack of available parts for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can cause serious injury or death.

airbag system malfunction
short in the right seat frame
